Task
Choose the attraction-building intent in the spoken line.
- Return NONE when the line is practical, neutral, guarded, or purely friendly.
- Return WARM when the line reaches toward closeness, praise, tenderness, personal interest, or emotional openness.
- Return FLIRTY when the line clearly plays with romantic or charged tension, invitation, teasing intimacy, or direct desire.
- Base the choice on the spoken line first, using the other context only to interpret it.
- Return exactly one label: NONE, WARM, or FLIRTY.

